cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

This paper proposes a method to improve the performance of LSTM in natural language processing tasks by introducing a dynamic skip connection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The proposed method also involves reinforcement learning, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves modeling sequential data, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the proposed method is evaluated on natural language processing tasks, which could also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
